The paper deals with cross-modal retrieval, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are likely categories. The paper also discusses hashing techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval, suggesting cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another possible category. The paper proposes a new framework for learning discriminative hash codes, which involves machine learning techniques, indicating cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-view features, which are commonly used in multimedia analysis, suggesting cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category.
